<!-- 03 — TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Makes JennAir Different — And How It Fails</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">JennAir's technology decisions are design-forward — which creates specific service requirements that generic appliance repair misses.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>25,000 BTU Brass Burners (RISE)</strong> — The highest output burner in the residential market. The brass construction and high thermal load creates specific igniter wear patterns. Igniter ceramic tips on 25K BTU burners degrade faster than on standard burners — we inspect and proactively replace before failure in annual maintenance.</li>
        <li><strong>V2™ Vertical Dual-Fan Convection</strong> — Two vertically-stacked convection fans that circulate air in a vertical pattern, eliminating the hot/cool spots that single horizontal fans create. When one fan fails, baking is uneven in a vertical pattern — top shelf different from bottom shelf, rather than side-to-side. We test each fan motor independently before recommending the assembly.</li>
        <li><strong>JennAir Culinary Center Touchscreen</strong> — The glass-covered touch interface for recipe guidance, temperature control, and smart connectivity. Cooking steam condensation behind the glass is the primary failure mechanism — the condensation disrupts the capacitive layer. Panel replacement (not full control board) resolves most touch failures.</li>
        <li><strong>Obsidian Interior (NOIR)</strong> — The dark matte finish inside NOIR ovens and dishwashers is more scratch-sensitive than standard enamel. During service, we never use abrasive cloths or scraping tools inside NOIR appliances. Parts installation in NOIR interiors requires extra care around the finish edges.</li>
        <li><strong>Downdraft Lift Mechanism</strong> — The retractable downdraft panel that lifts from the cooktop surface uses a motorized lift mechanism that JennAir has refined since 1961. Most common failure: the motor loses torque over time, causing sluggish retraction or failure to fully extend. We replace the motor assembly, not just the belt.</li>
        <li><strong>Cinematic LED Lighting (NOIR)</strong> — LED array systems in NOIR refrigerators and dishwashers that create a dramatic "theater opening" effect when doors are opened. The LED driver board is the most common failure point. Replacement is model-specific — we source OEM JennAir lighting assemblies through Whirlpool's supply network.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🌊 LA + JennAir RISE</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">The 25,000 BTU brass burners that make RISE distinctive also create accelerated igniter wear in coastal LA environments. Salt air corrosion on the higher-temperature ceramic tip progresses faster than on standard burners. Properties in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach should include igniter inspection in annual maintenance. We check RISE burner tip condition on every service call.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#1a0a0a; border-color:var(--red); margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label">⬛ NOIR Dishwasher — Noise = News</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">JennAir NOIR's dishwasher runs at 38 dBA — one of the quietest on the market. Any noise from a NOIR dishwasher is instantly noticeable to the owner and almost always indicates something specific: pump impeller debris (grinding), loose motor mount (vibration), or Obsidian rack contact (clicking). We diagnose by noise character before opening the unit.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common JennAir Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">📱 Culinary Center Touch Panel Unresponsive</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Cooking steam condensation behind the glass panel disrupts the capacitive layer — certain zones stop responding while others work normally. This is a panel failure, not a control board failure. Replacing the panel (not the full board) resolves most cases. We test the control board separately to confirm before ordering the panel.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 RISE Brass Burner Won't Ignite</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">25,000 BTU brass burners run hotter than standard burners — the ceramic igniter tip experiences higher thermal cycling stress. Coastal LA accelerates this further with salt air corrosion. The igniter is geometry-specific for the high-output brass burner configuration — generic replacements don't fit correctly at this BTU level.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-rise">RISE Collection</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Baking Unevenly (V2 Fan)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">One of the two V2 vertical fans has failed. The pattern is diagnostic: uneven results that vary top-to-bottom indicate a V2 fan issue, while side-to-side variation suggests a single-fan convection problem. We test each fan motor's speed and current draw independently before recommending parts.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">⬛ NOIR Cinematic Lighting Dead</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">The LED driver board in NOIR refrigerators and dishwashers fails independently of the main control board. The "cinematic opening" effect disappears entirely when the driver fails. OEM replacement is model-specific — the LED assembly differs between NOIR refrigerator and dishwasher models. We carry common driver boards for current NOIR models.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-noir">NOIR Collection</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💨 Downdraft Won't Lift or Retract</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Downdraft lift motor torque loss — the motor weakens gradually, causing sluggish or incomplete extension and retraction. Left unaddressed, the motor eventually stops entirely. We replace the lift motor assembly (not just the drive mechanism) for a complete repair that lasts. The downdraft fan and filter are inspected simultaneously.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">❄️ Column Refrigerator Not Cooling</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">JennAir RISE and NOIR column refrigerators use the Whirlpool sealed system platform. Most cooling failures trace to condenser coil dust accumulation (LA particulate is significant on hillside and Valley properties), thermistor failure, or a defrost system fault. We diagnose by checking coil condition first — it resolves the majority of cases without parts.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Environment</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

